How @{b}tar@{ub} Archives are Named
==========================

   Conventionally, @{b}tar@{ub} archives are given names ending with @{b}.tar@{ub}.  This
is not necessary for @{b}tar@{ub} to operate properly, but this manual follows
that convention in order to accustom readers to it and to make examples
more clear.

   Often, people refer to @{b}tar@{ub} archives as "@{b}tar@{ub} files," and archive
members as "files" or "entries".  For people familiar with the
operation of @{b}tar@{ub}, this causes no difficulty.  However, in this manual,
we consistently refer to "archives" and "archive members" to make
learning to use @{b}tar@{ub} easier for novice users.


@endnode

