   This chapter documents both the provided FSF scripts and @{b}tar@{ub} options
which are more specific to usage as a backup tool.

   To @{i}back up@{ui} a file system means to create archives that contain all
the files in that file system.  Those archives can then be used to
restore any or all of those files (for instance if a disk crashes or a
file is accidently deleted).  File system @{i}backups@{ui} are also called @{i}dumps@{ui}.


